entries.femaleVariant: No, you're feeding me scop and you know it. A third-gen Kiroshi with first-gen muscles?! You're just asking for a full sys meltdown!
Exactly the setup I got right now, and you don't see me complain. Just gotta tweak the soft a bit.
What, they pay you by the unit sold, or are you just trying to clear up storage!?
Listen, the problem's not with the implant. It's the software. Kiroshi keeps it incompatible, so gonks gotta swap their muscle weaves every two years.
Truth is, Kiroshi sends the signal normal, but bam! Soft blocks it. It's all about eddies, nothing else.
Hmm, well... How do you mod it, then?
Well! If you're interested, I can recommend a good runner, and I'll give you a little discount on this implant.
